# API Conventions

## Route Structure

```
app/api/
  v1/
    concepts.py      # /api/v1/concepts
    edges.py         # /api/v1/edges
    items.py         # /api/v1/items
    groups.py        # /api/v1/groups
    data_entities.py # /api/v1/data-entities
    traversal.py     # /api/v1/traversal
    ai_services.py   # /api/v1/ai
```

## Endpoint Rules

- All routes versioned under `/api/v1/`.
- Use plural nouns for resource paths (`/entities`, not `/entity`).
- Return Pydantic response models — never return raw dicts.
- Use dependency injection for services, DB sessions, and auth:

```python
@router.get("/{entity_id}", response_model=EntityResponse)
async def get_entity(
    entity_id: str,
    service: EntityService = Depends(get_entity_service),
    current_user: User = Depends(get_current_user),
) -> EntityResponse:
    ...
```

## HTTP Status Codes

| Action | Success | Failure |
|--------|---------|---------|
| GET    | 200     | 404     |
| POST   | 201     | 400/422 |
| PUT    | 200     | 404/422 |
| DELETE | 204     | 404     |

## Validation

- Request validation via Pydantic models in `app/schemas/`.
- Never validate manually in route handlers — let the schema do it.
